---
description: Stripe is for shop or web checkout only
globs: ["**/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx,json}"]
alwaysApply: true
---

Stripe may be used only for shop or web-only checkout flows, not for in-app coin purchases.

Rules:
- use Stripe only for shop, web checkout, or browser-based purchase flows explicitly intended for web
- do not use Stripe as the payment mechanism for in-app mobile coin purchases
- do not replace Android or iOS IAP flows with Stripe
- do not connect existing in-app coin buttons directly to Stripe
- if the repository has a separate shop flow, preserve it as separate from in-app purchases
- do not blur the boundary between in-app currency purchases and external shop checkout
- preserve current UI and layout while wiring logic
- do not invent Stripe usage where it does not already belong

Allowed:
- connect shop checkout buttons to Stripe if the flow is clearly a shop/web flow
- fix broken Stripe wiring in shop-related code only
- improve checkout error handling
- improve loading and redirect handling without visual redesign

Default behavior:
Stripe is limited to shop-only flows, not mobile in-app coins.
